And where was that?
It was in La Jolla, and it was an art film theater.
Repertory Film Theater and a bookstore.
And out of, really, my husband's collecting books and our realization that the old illustrated books were essentially out of everybody's knowledge.
I mean, they were out of print and rare and not being reprinted or anything.
And some of the great illustrators of the past, Rackham and so forth, were just
basically unknown to all except a few antiquarians.
We started the Green Tiger Press, which originally started with reproducing old illustrations out of our collection.
Collection of what, specifically?
Of illustrated books.
Illustrated books.
And then it went from there.
The first book we published was a book by my husband about children's illustrations.
or illustrations in children's books, and called All Mirrors or Magic Mirrors.
And then we printed, we did reprints all the way through the Green Tigress history, and then we started doing modern illustrators with modern stories.

Harold.
Harold.
Harold.

New London, Connecticut.

A lot of Navy people do.

And so anyway, the Green Tiger Press was really born out of my interest in training as a painter.
I come from a family of a lot of painters.

professional in the art field, all the way down to my sister, who's a successful artist in Canada.
